            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000024211/Kaufman and Selser, Navajo Weaving Tradition (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Alfombras de tapicería tejidas navajo que representa a yeibichai, bailarines navajos que personifican el yei o pueblo sagrado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
